messages.body:
Early polling results (72% of votes counted) in California look friendly to REITs. Voters are on pace to reject two propositions on the ballot, which would have mostly impacted Office and Multifamily REITs: Prop 15, related to split roll taxes (current count at 52% no); Prop 21, related to residential rent control (current 60% voting no). 

Top portfolios exposed to California:

$DEI (89%) $KRC (88%) $HPP (87%) $ESS (83%) $EQR (47%)

$ACI Was looking at buying REITs. Then I realized this is kind of a REIT. Huge property holdings, dividend, and undervalued to boot. And yeah, no rent collection issues lol. (I did end up buying $EQR, $MPW, $WRE, $WPC, too)

$WRE Hit new lows recently. With almost 100 percent rent collection IIRC. DC is one of the most stable commercial and residential markets in country, even growing. Ridiculous. Also like $EQR, $MPW. Buy the fear. In my metro, city apartments are being snapped up fast. Real assets are real assets. Urbanization trends centuries in making don't evaporate overnight.
Does this make you nervous? $EQR in Uptrend: price may jump up because it broke its lower Bollinger Band on October 28, 2020. View odds for this and other indicators: https://srnk.us/go/2282042
